</code></pre>
<p>I think this is actually more in the spirit of a unit test. Like I said though, I’ll keep searching for a bit.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2022-01-15T23:07:30.261Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":20.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":400367,"topic_slug":"trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java","display_username":"Bart Kerfeld","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":50780,"username":"OccultSlolem","name":"Ethan Hanlon","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/8491ac/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":19314,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java/400367/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2992440,"name":"Ethan Hanlon","username":"OccultSlolem","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/8491ac/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-01-15T23:04:48.522Z","cooked":"<p>Oh lol, can’t believe I never thought of that <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/joy.png?v=9" title=":joy:" class="emoji" alt=":joy:"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/joy.png?v=9" title=":joy:" class="emoji" alt=":joy:"></p>
<p>If it <em>is</em> possible to use the scheduler for unit tests that would be nice, although I suppose it would be easier to simply use this method. Cheers.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2022-01-15T23:04:48.522Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":400367,"topic_slug":"trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java","display_username":"Ethan Hanlon","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":19314,"username":"Bart_Kerfeld","name":"Bart Kerfeld","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bart_kerfeld/{size}/156555_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50780,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java/400367/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2992443,"name":null,"username":"Starlight220","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/starlight220/{size}/150872_2.png","created_at":"2022-01-15T23:07:33.754Z","cooked":"<p>Have you read the Unit Testing page in the documentation? There might be something there that you missed.</p>
