<p>I’m probably going to be writing some sim / unit tests myself tomorrow, so if I find a fix for this then I’ll let you know.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2022-01-15T23:07:33.754Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":400367,"topic_slug":"trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":45763,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6738a | ISR | WPILib"},"post_url":"/t/trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java/400367/8","custom_user_title":"6738a | ISR | WPILib","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2992444,"name":"Ethan Hanlon","username":"OccultSlolem","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/8491ac/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-01-15T23:08:30.150Z","cooked":"<p>I read it like 5 times. It doesn’t cover testing <em>commands</em> unfortunately. I saw <a href="https://firstmncsa.org/2019/09/16/unit-testing-commands/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">this tutorial from 2019</a> that I wasn’t able to replicate unfortunately, although I’m not using Mockito here unlike they were.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2022-01-15T23:08:30.150Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":50,"readers_count":49,"score":15.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":400367,"topic_slug":"trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java","display_username":"Ethan Hanlon","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://firstmncsa.org/2019/09/16/unit-testing-commands/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Unit Testing Commands | FirstMnCsa","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":45763,"username":"Starlight220","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/starlight220/{size}/150872_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50780,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/trouble-unit-testing-commands-in-java/400367/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2992446,"name":"Joe Ross","username":"Joe_Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png","created_at":"2022-01-15T23:11:12.537Z","cooked":"<p>There’s multiple conditions in that statement that all need to be false for it to be scheduled. Since a DS isn’t running, the commands runsWhenDisabled also needs to be true.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2022-01-15T23:11:12.537Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":49,"readers_count":48,"score":29.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":400367,"topic_